article.headline: Toledo 68, E. Michigan 56
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio (AP) -- Kashif Payne hit two of his three 3-pointers in a 15-3 run that put Toledo up for good in a 68-56 victory Tuesday night over Eastern Michigan. Payne finished with 13 points, and Florentino Valencia and Keonta Howell each added 12 points for the Rockets (14-10, 10-2 Mid-American). Eastern Michigan was up 30-26 at the half and had it tied at 45-45 with 10:13 left, but the Rockets' run, capped by a Valencia layup, put Toledo up 60-48 with 6:48 left. The Eagles didn't come closer than 9 after that. Devon Dumes scored 15 points, making 5 of 8 3-pointers, and Brandon Bowdry scored 12 for the Eagles (9-16, 4-8). Toledo outscored Eastern Michigan 36-16 in the paint and 31-17 in points off turnovers.
